Key Match Events: Milwaukee Bucks dominated Toronto Raptors with a 128-104 victory
Damian Lillard led the scoring effort for Milwaukee with 25 points
Bobby Portis came off the bench with an impactful performance, contributing 20 points
Post-Match Reflections: Giannis Antetokounmpo's historic scoring streak of 27 consecutive games with 20 or more points on at least 50% shooting from the field ended
Antetokounmpo finished with 11 points, 13 assists, and 12 rebounds, marking his third triple-double of the season
Miscellaneous Highlights: Milwaukee knocked down 22 three-pointers while shooting 50% from beyond the arc
The Bucks' ball movement was exceptional, tallying 37 assists as a team
Others: Milwaukee held the Raptors to 45.1% shooting from the field
The Bucks are now sitting fifth in the Eastern Conference standings
The team will look to build on this momentum in their next game against the San Antonio Spurs
